## Module 5

1\. You are developing a high-performance computing (HPC) application for real-time data processing, where multiple data streams are processed concurrently. OpenMP is used to manage the workload effectively across available cores. Evaluate the code and suggest the best strategy for using OpenMP to balance the workload and ensure timely processing of data streams.  
![][image1]

1. **Use \#pragma omp parallel for to parallelize processing of each stream, ensuring all streams are handled simultaneously.**  
2. Apply \#pragma omp sections for processing independent data chunks within each stream.  
3. Use \#pragma omp single to avoid contention and improve data coherence.  
4. Implement \#pragma omp task for dynamic scheduling of stream processing.  
5. Rely on operating system scheduling instead of OpenMP for real-time performance.
